{"action": "edit", "code": "def fill_pixels_around_yellow_with_blue(yellow_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the grid and an input grid, \n    fills the 8 pixels around each yellow pixel with blue color and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    yellow_pixels: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with the 8 pixels around each yellow pixel filled with blue color.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i, j in yellow_pixels:\n        for x in range(i - 1, i + 2):\n            for y in range(j - 1, j + 2):\n                if (x, y) != (i, j) and 0 <= x < input_grid.shape[0] and (0 <= y < input_grid.shape[1]):\n                    input_grid[x][y] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef find_yellow_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    yellow_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == yellow:\n                yellow_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return yellow_pixels\ndef fill_pixels_around_blue_with_yellow(blue_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the grid and an input grid, \n    fills the 8 pixels around each blue pixel with yellow color and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    blue_pixels: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with the 8 pixels around each blue pixel filled with yellow color.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i, j in blue_pixels:\n        for x in range(i - 1, i + 2):\n            for y in range(j - 1, j + 2):\n                if (x, y) != (i, j) and 0 <= x < input_grid.shape[0] and (0 <= y < input_grid.shape[1]):\n                    input_grid[x][y] = yellow\n    return input_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blueloc = find_blue_pixels(input_grid)\n    yellowloc = find_yellow_pixels(input_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_around_blue_with_yellow(blueloc, input_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_around_yellow_with_blue(yellowloc, output_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_around_blue_and_yellow(blueloc, yellowloc, output_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef find_blue_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == blue:\n                blue_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return blue_pixels\ndef fill_pixels_around_blue_and_yellow(blue_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]], yellow_pixels: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels and yellow pixels in the grid and an input grid, \n    fills the 8 pixels around each blue pixel with yellow color an