{"action": "edit", "code": "def fill_pixels_around_yellow_with_blue(yellowloc: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the input grid,\n    fills the 8 pixels around each yellow pixel with blue color and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    yellowloc: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the input grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with 8 pixels around each yellow pixel filled with blue color.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i, j in yellowloc:\n        for x in range(i - 1, i + 2):\n            for y in range(j - 1, j + 2):\n                if 0 <= x < input_grid.shape[0] and 0 <= y < input_grid.shape[1]:\n                    input_grid[x][y] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef find_yellow_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    yellow_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == yellow:\n                yellow_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return yellow_pixels\ndef fill_pixels_around_blue_with_yellow(blueloc: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the input grid,\n    fills the 8 pixels around each blue pixel with yellow color and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    blueloc: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the input grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with 8 pixels around each blue pixel filled with yellow color.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i, j in blueloc:\n        for x in range(i - 1, i + 2):\n            for y in range(j - 1, j + 2):\n                if 0 <= x < input_grid.shape[0] and 0 <= y < input_grid.shape[1]:\n                    input_grid[x][y] = yellow\n    return input_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blueloc = find_blue_pixels(input_grid)\n    yellowloc = find_yellow_pixels(input_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_around_blue_with_yellow(blueloc, input_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_around_yellow_with_blue(yellowloc, output_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_with_blue(blueloc, output_grid)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_with_yellow(yellowloc, output_grid)\n    left, right, up, down = find_blue_edges(blueloc)\n    output_grid = fill_pixels_with_grey(left, right, up, down, output_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef fill_pixels_with_grey(left: int, right: int, up: int, down: int, input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the left, right, up, and down indices of the blue edges in the input grid, fills specific pixels with grey color\n    and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    left: An integer representing the left index of the blue edges in the input grid.\n    right: An integer representing the right index of the blue edges in the input grid.\n    up: An integer representing the up index of the blue edges in the input grid.\n    down: An integer representing the down index of the blue edges in the input grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with specific pixels filled with grey color.\n    \"\"\"\n    input_grid[left, up + 2] = grey\n    input_grid[left, up + 4] = grey\n    input_grid[left, down - 2] = grey\n    input_grid[left, down - 4] = grey\n    input_grid[right, up + 2] = grey\n    input_grid[right, up + 4] = grey\n    input_grid[right, down - 2] = grey\n    input_grid[right, down - 4] = grey\n    input_grid[left + 2, up] = grey\n    input_grid[left + 4, up] = grey\n    input_grid[right - 2, up] = grey\n    input_grid[right - 4, up] = grey\n    input_grid[left + 2, down] = grey\n    input_grid[left + 4, down] = grey\n    input_grid[right - 2, down] = grey\n    input_grid[right - 4, down] = grey\n    return input_grid\ndef fill_pixels_with_blue(blueloc: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the input grid,\n    fills all the pixels with blue color and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    blueloc: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the input grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with all blue pixels filled with blue color.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i, j in blueloc:\n        input_grid[i][j] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef fill_pixels_with_yellow(yellowloc: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the input grid,\n    fills all the pixels with yellow color and returns the updated grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    yellowloc: A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all yellow pixels in the input grid.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid with all yellow pixels filled with yellow color.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i, j in yellowloc:\n        input_grid[i][j] = yellow\n    return input_grid\ndef find_blue_edges(blueloc: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> Tuple[int, int, int, int]:\n    left = min(blueloc, key=lambda x: x[1])[1]\n    right = max(blueloc, key=lambda x: x[1])[1]\n    up = min(blueloc, key=lambda x: x[0])[0]\n    down = max(blueloc, key=lambda x: x[0])[0]\n    return (left, right, up, down)\ndef find_blue_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns a list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the (row, column) indices of all blue pixels in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_pixels = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == blue:\n                blue_pixels.append((i, j))\n    return blue_pixels", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blueloc = `find all blue pixels`(input_grid)\n    yellowloc = `find all yellow pixels`(input_grid)\n    output_grid = `fill the 8 pixels around blueloc with yellow`(blueloc, input_grid)\n    output_grid = `fill the 8 pixels around yellowloc with blue`(yellowloc, output_grid)\n    output_grid = `fill blueloc with blue`(blueloc, output_grid)\n    output_grid = ` fill yellowloc with yellow`(yellowloc, output_grid)\n    left, right, up, down = `find the left, right, up, down edge of blueloc, and return the colomn number and row number`(blueloc) \n    output_grid = `fill the following pixels with grey: (left, up+2), (left, up+4), (left, down-2), (left, down-4),(right, up+2), (right, up+4), (right, down-2), (right, down-4), (left+2, up), (left+4, up), (right-2, up), (right-4, up),(left+2, down), (left+4, down), (right-2, down), (right-4, down)`(left, right, up, down, output_grid)\n    return output_grid", "gpt_code": "def fill_pixels_around_yellow_with_blue(yellowloc: List[Tuple[int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Giv